Proposed timetable:
# TravelPlan: Stuttgart to Prague ultra-budget solo trip, 20–23 June 2026

| Day 1 — 2026-06-20 — Arrival + Old Town first walk | Day 2 — 2026-06-21 — Old Town, Jewish Quarter + Castle viewpoints | Day 3 — 2026-06-22 — Vyšehrad + riverside budget day | Day 4 — 2026-06-23 — Final morning + return to Stuttgart |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **1. Target carpool: Stuttgart → Prague Florenc** [transport] 08:00–14:00 @ Stuttgart Hbf/SAB → ÚAN Florenc, Prague (€29.00) — Budget target: book a BlaBlaCar seat 2–14 days before departure; typical duration about 5h49 and estimated seat price €19–€29. Fixed backup: early-book FlixBus from Stuttgart Airport/North to Prague Florenc, usually €32.50+ one-way. Time is a practical planning window; confirm the exact driver or bus time when booking. — Links: [link 1](https://www.blablacar.com/), [link 2](https://www.flixbus.com/bus-routes/bus-prague-stuttgart) | **1. Hostel/simple breakfast** [meal] 08:00–08:30 @ Hostel Florenc / Florenc supermarket (€4.00) — Use hostel breakfast if included; otherwise buy supermarket rolls/yogurt/fruit. | **1. Hostel/simple breakfast** [meal] 08:00–08:30 @ Hostel Florenc / Florenc supermarket (€4.00) — Cheap hostel/supermarket breakfast: rolls, yogurt, fruit, or included hostel breakfast if available. | **1. Hostel/simple breakfast** [meal] 08:00–08:30 @ Hostel Florenc / Florenc supermarket (€4.00) — Final cheap breakfast from hostel breakfast or supermarket/bakery food. |
| **2. Walk Florenc bus station → Hostel Florenc** [transport] 14:00–14:10 @ ÚAN Florenc to Hostel Florenc (€0.00) — Free 5-minute walk, about 331–359 m, from ÚAN Florenc to the hostel on Pod výtopnou. — Links: [link 1](https://www.rome2rio.com/s/Florenc-Bus-Station/Hotel-Florenc-Prague) | **2. Walk to free walking tour meeting area** [transport] 08:30–09:00 @ Hostel Florenc → Old Town / Powder Tower (€0.00) — Walk from Florenc to Old Town Square/Powder Tower area. The hostel-to-Old-Town walk is under 20 minutes; arrive early for a pre-booked tip-based tour. | **2. Walk Hostel Florenc → Vítkov Hill** [transport] 08:30–09:00 @ Hostel Florenc → Vítkov Hill (€0.00) — Walk from Florenc/Karlín up toward Vítkov; free local transit and a useful viewpoint route. | **2. Check out and store/keep backpack** [lodging] 08:30–09:00 @ Hostel Florenc (€0.00) — Check out by the hostel deadline. Avoid paid luggage storage if possible by carrying a small backpack; if needed, use hostel luggage room only if free. |
| **3. Check in: Hostel Florenc shared dorm** [lodging] 14:10–14:40 @ Hostel Florenc, Pod výtopnou 163/10, Prague (€93.00) — Shared dorm base next to Florenc bus station; live hotel search found Sir Toby’s at €31/night, while Hostel Florenc is the more location-efficient target near the arrival terminal. Budget assumes €31/night x 3 nights plus local tax separately. — Links: [link 1](https://travelstack.nuitee.link/hotels/lp4eae0?checkin=2026-06-20&checkout=2026-06-23&rooms=1&adults=1&occupancies=W3siYWR1bHRzIjoxLCJjaGlsZHJlbiI6W119XQ%3D%3D&language=de&currency=EUR) | **3. Tip-based Old Town + Jewish Quarter walking tour** [attraction] 09:00–11:30 @ Old Town Square / Josefov, Prague (€10.00) — Tip-based historical walk covering Old Town, Jewish Quarter exteriors, Charles Bridge context, Astronomical Clock, and medieval lanes. No upfront fee; budget a modest €10 tip. — Links: [link 1](https://freewalkingtourprague.eu/en/schedule), [link 2](https://www.google.com/maps/search/Guruwalk+S.L.) | **3. Vítkov Hill + National Monument exterior** [attraction] 09:00–11:30 @ Vítkov, Žižkov, Prague (€0.00) — Free historical viewpoint over Žižkov and Karlín, with the Jan Žižka equestrian statue and National Monument exterior. The outdoor park/viewpoint costs nothing; skip paid museum interiors. — Links: [link 1](https://www.google.com/maps/search/Vítkov) | **3. Final free Old Town wander / souvenir-free morning** [attraction] 09:00–11:30 @ Florenc → Old Town / Na Příkopě / riverside (€0.00) — Walk the free central route again: Powder Tower exterior, Municipal House exterior, Old Town lanes, and riverside if weather is good. No paid towers or museums. — Links: [link 1](https://www.google.com/maps/search/Old+Town+Square+Prague) |
